headline: Mastercard poised to buy crypto firm Zerohash for nearly $2 billion, Fortune reports
summary: Mastercard is in late-stage talks to acquire crypto startup Zerohash for between $1.5 billion and $2 billion, Fortune reported on Wednesday, citing five sources familiar with the matter. If the deal goes through, it would be Mastercard's one of the biggest bets yet on stablecoins, the report said, adding the talks might still fall through. Mastercard and Zerohash did not immediately respond to Reuters' requests for comment.

headline: Mastercard introduces first-ever threat intelligence solution to combat payment fraud at scale
summary: Today, Mastercard announced the launch of Mastercard Threat Intelligence, the first threat intelligence offering applied to payments at scale. The solution combines Mastercard's global fraud insights with cyber threat intelligence from Recorded Future, empowering financial institutions across Asia-Pacific (APAC) to detect, prevent and respond to cyber-enabled fraud with greater speed and accuracy.
